body:
I found no way to enlarge the clipping area of the "SKCanvas" object. Even if I use the "SKRegion" class to get the desired region, I can't pass it to the SKCanvas object. The SKClipOperation enumeration parameter used by the existing method of setting the clipping region can only shrink the clipping region.
Is it that I didn't find the right way?

If the truth is what I say.
I personally recommend replacing the parameter 'SKClipOperation' in the method of the SKCanvas class with 'SKRegionOperation' to set the clipping region.

**We are evaluating whether we can use the skiasharp library in our product, so hope to hear back soon. 
Thank you very much!**

My code:
```
int sw = 800, sh = 800;
SKBitmap sKBitmap = new SKBitmap(sw, sh);
using (SKCanvas canvas = new SKCanvas(sKBitmap))
{
    canvas.Clear(SKColor.Empty);
    SKPaint redPaint = new SKPaint() {
        Color = SKColors.Red,
        IsStroke = true,
        StrokeWidth = 1
    };
    SKPaint greenPaint = new SKPaint() {
        Color = SKColors.Green,
        IsStroke = true,
        StrokeWidth = 1
    };
    SKPaint bluePaint = new SKPaint() {
        Color = SKColors.Blue,
        IsStroke = true,
        StrokeWidth = 1
    };

    canvas.DrawLine(new SKPoint(0, 0), new SKPoint(600, 600), greenPaint);
    canvas.DrawLine(new SKPoint(600, 0), new SKPoint(0, 600), bluePaint);

    SKRectI clipRect = new SKRectI(0, 0, 200, 200);
    SKRectI intersectRectF = new SKRectI(100, 100, 300, 300);
    canvas.DrawRect(clipRect, bluePaint);
    canvas.DrawRect(intersectRectF, greenPaint);


    canvas.ClipRect(clipRect);//set 1
    
    //do something
    canvas.DrawColor(SKColors.Green);
    
    canvas.ClipRect(intersectRectF);//set 2

    //do something
    canvas.DrawColor(SKColors.Red);

    sKBitmap.Encode(new SKFileWStream("testClip.png"), SKEncodedImageFormat.Png, 100);
}
```
after set2:
How to get an area larger than the current clipping area？
How to get the area that sets the current clipping area to the entire canvas？
